entries.femaleVariant: So this is the place…
Eighth floor?
I need to apologize.
For...?
She's capable of takin' care of herself, you know.
C'mon, c'mon…! Don't do this!
Just stop! He's gone, dead, done!
Relax, she ain't alone. Made some new chooms. Locals.
I'd offer to sit down and chat over coffee, but the clock's tickin'.
Not doin' this for the eddies.
Some things're more important than eddies, Reed.
Doin' this 'cause I need to survive.
Songbird's my only shot at survivin'.
It seems we're all on the same page now, V.
Said she'd meet us here, and... has given no sign of life since.
Lead the way.
This shit runs deeper, Reed.
V was the last person to talk to her.
Song disappeared after the crash.
Songbird needs your help.
Stay safe.
Buy me a nice dinner sometime.
Stay safe, 'n' don't let the bastards getcha.
Buy me a nice dinner sometime.
Same to you, V.
May we meet again in more favorable circumstances.
Hah! You do this often – invite presidents out on dates?
Often enough.
Okay. Dinner it'll be.
Just gotta survive till then…
Good luck, V.
It's your fuckin' fault!
This keeps gettin' worse and worse....
This wasn't suposeta happen…
Then why Frank's dead, huh?! Fuck…!
Don't move a muscle!
Level with me, Rosalind. You never intended to call that line.
Well, I found myself in Night City with a bounty on my head…
So it seemed the right moment to reach out, have a tête-à-tête, reset an old friendship.
Can you drop two?
That's enough, gentlemen!
I dunno… It's askin' for trouble.
Just think. Buildin's been empty for years. Why? 'Cause Hansen--
Hansen this, Hansen that – I'ma fuckin' lose it, choom.
Open up. It's me.
Are you sure?
If anyone had tried to extract her forcibly, this whole level'd be in shambles. No way she would've gone quietly.
Yo! Watch where you goin'!
If you're not using those optics, I have a buyer for 'em.
Mh. You remembered my number.
Some numbers you never forget.
Yeah.
Introductions were a little dicey, but she turned on the charm. Probably has her Dogtown campaign staff by now.
Sometimes that's the only way out…
I fully expected you to walk us into an ambush.
Honestly? This is not inspiring confidence.
Actually had uninvited guests last night. Ejected via the garbage chute.
Look around. Positive.
Put your tools away, gents. Compare length and girth when I'm not around.
You the boss.
I'm good. Glad to see you are, too.
Is this how you greet me?
Uhh…
Sorry. Rosalind - are you all right?
I'm fine. But I heard shots…
Besides… She's your prodigy, Sol. You taught her all your tricks, hell, even "recruited" her.
Yeah, yeah, comin'…
I need to arrange passage for you to Washington.
Come on, we should talk in private.
The president, a merc and a special agent walk into the Oval Office …
You've seen the news.
Everything all right?
All good, Jacob?
Doggone fairytale, V…
I need to arrange a safe passage to Washington for Myers. Expect my call soon, V.
If we want to find So Mi, we gotta dig deep. I mean actual reconnaissance, no stone unturned.
We need contacts, informers not afraid to sing, who might see somethin' in it for themselves.
You'll need to earn their trust.
Big ask in Dogtown. Won't be easy.
Alright, I need to make some calls.
Thanks. For everything.
Made my decision.
Finally showin' me your true face.
That the way of things? Hard pass from me, then. If I gotta die, I'm not gonna die fightin' someone else's war.
entries.maleVariant: That the way of things, huh? Hard pass from me, then. If I gotta die, I'm not gonna die fightin' someone else's war.

entries.femaleVariant: I see. Well, we'll manage without you.
Mhmm.
Don't let the door hit you on the way out.
Sounds like total blackmail… but it worked.
Blatant fuckin' blackmail, as I see it.
But fine. It worked.
Good. I'm glad.
Gotta apologize – for Reed.
You'll have to excuse my friend, he's... sometimes... excitable.
entries.maleVariant: You'll have to excuse my friend, he's sometimes... excitable.

entries.femaleVariant: Riiight… You ought to teach him about the value of initial impressions.
Somethin's off 'bout them. S'like they say – if it ain't about sex, 's about power.
Fuck's sake… again?!
Here.
You earned my trust. It wasn't easy, but you did it.
Question is, where do I fit into this joke?
Post crash, Songbird vanished.
No, Reed. We need to talk first. All three of us.
Something bad happened mid-op.
I wasn't alone on that flight.
Songbird was on board, too.
She was coordinating our escape, guiding us. Something happened mid-op.
Elaborate.
We have no idea. We're treating her as MIA.
Whatever the case, it's fucking bad news.
So what do you think happened?
Where is she?
That we agree on.
Shit, choom's lookin' like bad news…
Take point.
[Knock door] It's me.
Open up. It's me.
You're right. I'm out.
Know what, Reed? You're right.
Somethin' real wonky 'bout this. I'm out.
Where is she now?
So Mi…?
I had a bad feeling about this. But now… now I see why…
You two have to find her. Together.
Got a debt to pay, Rosalind.
I'm sorry, Reed. For those seven years.
Uh-huh. Hansen's spinwork never fails to amuse.
He's not acting purely on his own initiative. Someone from our camp's propping him up.
And she and V have a unique... bond. It's a lead, our only one for now.
I'm here, I'll help. But I'm doin' it for So Mi… and my country. Call me naive if you like.
You're right.
Every moment we spend poutin' here, our chances of finding So Mi alive drop. Hard.
entries.maleVariant: Look, every moment we spend poutin' here, our chances of finding So Mi alive drop. Hard.

entries.femaleVariant: Lemme get this straight… You abandon Reed in NC, leave 'im for dead, and now expect 'im to jump right back into shit?
Newsflash, Madame President – got a helluva debt to pay.
Is that enough... to get us a fresh start?
We all got our reasons. Mine's even got a name – the Relic. If I don't find So Mi, I'm literally a dead woman.
entries.maleVariant: We all got our reasons. Mine's even got a name – the Relic. If I don't find So Mi, I'm literally a dead man.

entries.femaleVariant: Smellin' some real bad blood between you two. Time to settle this beef?
Reed doesn't trust me. I can't say I blame him.
You two prolly gotta talk things over.
Whaddaya mean you "died"?
Whaddaya mean you "died" already?
What has Myers told you about me?
I already died for the cause once. Not enough?
Like… she was attacked? Dunno, hard to describe.
Said you'd led an intelligence cell here, went into hibernation at war's end.
entries.maleVariant: Said you led an intelligence cell here, went into hibernation at war's end.

entries.femaleVariant: So she omitted the fact that Arasaka tried to smoke me?
That I ended up in intensive care with three bullet holes?
That six months had passed before I could take a shit on my own?
Might've... slipped her mind…
Convenient. Well now you know.
I abandoned him in NC seven years ago. He's been stuck here, paid a high price.
The NUSA crushed his career, while Arasaka tried hard to have him garrotted.
Barely know ya, but you don't seem like a choom who would leave their agent out to dry. She won't survive without backup.
[Shake his hand] Think so, too.
We'll see about that.
Agreed. Think so too, Reed.
Gotta wait and see, won't we?
Got Arasaka's Relic in my head, slowly, surely poaching my brain.
Which means we can help each other, too.
I heard So Mi was on board.
Hansen's gangoons… Must've spotted you, tracks you left.
Could've seen us on NC metro camfeeds.
Somebody ratted us out.
Must've tagged us off metro camfeeds…
Somebody ratted us out. Got my suspects already.
Let's hope we can correct it.
And you let 'em live?
We need to take those fools down and hope we're not too late.
Think BARGHEST checks every dilapidated shithole, pissin', markin' their territory?
Cunt's squeezin' the 'hood by the balls 'n' chooms don't got no place to live. An' no one does a damn thing! Ya'll treat him like some fuckin' Dogtown boogeyman!
Did you ever think it might be the reason we're still kickin' about? Hmph, food for thought.
It feels like we've just seen the tip of the iceberg.
That all of 'em? Are there more?
Yeah, I-I-I… I think tha'ss all... Came outta nowhere!
They step foot in the buildin', you hide, y'hear me? Let us handle this.
Elevator. Find cover.
Sergeant!
Terminate 'em!
A friend...?
A friend.
Makes no difference now.
Yeah. Friend.
Doe'n't matter to him. What's it matter at all?
I understand.
I'm sorry.
Come on, V.
Some things never change.
What?
Wherever she goes, people get hurt, bodies drop.
Ever heard of a little thing called trust, choom?
In my line of work? That's nothing but a character flaw.
'S all good.
Sheesh, could stand to extend a little trust.
Don't worry 'bout it.
Glad I got it wrong.
Thanks.
Couple of guys came in last night, saw us.
Uh-huh.
Pacifism has a price, V.
A mistake. Happens to everyone.
This Rosalind chick? Piece o' work if I eva seen one. Thinkin' we mighta had a "moment."
Jacob and Taylor… They tried to defend…
We arrived too late.
Shit, I… huh…
Come on. Open it.
Who're these people?
Saw an army of drifters outside. Hell's up with that?
Word got out place's got electricity 'n' shit, I reckon.
Word just stood up and got out on its own?
Beats me, choomita!
Made any plans? What's next?
So, what's the future hold in store for J and T?
I guess it comes down to our dear Madame Prez. Will she keep her word?
Two options. We die in Dogtown, or we hit the road, scoot far, far outta here.
At least his kind goes guns blazing. I mean, screw those "stab-ya-in-the-backsters."
Gotta evac soon. Watch yourself out there, Jacob.
Gotta delta.
See, if I came knockin' last night, I'da missed a chance to meet my babe Rosalind. And you, I s'ppose.
Naw, the world better watch out for Jacob! Hahah!...
Just remember to knock 'fore you enter shady-lookin' digs.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, just remember to knock 'fore you enter any shady-lookin' digs.

entries.femaleVariant: Ahhh… that's life for ya, V.
There a lesson in all this, don'tcha think?
High time I headed out.
Gonna boost soon. Keep an eye on J, will ya?
One shitty nanny I'd make.
Eh. Keep it real, V.
Don't know me well, but well enough, I guess. I wouldn't.
Shame she ain't finna stay longer.
Songbird promised you help with the Relic. Now I will use any and all NUS assets to fulfill that promise. Consider it my contribution to your deal.
Walk out of here, and the deal's null and void – understood?
Now listen close, V. I'm only gonna say this once.
It's possible she hit ICE.
Most likely scenario - got caught in some ICE on the combat bot when she hacked it.
One little mishack, happens even to the best. But... no way to know for sure.
entries.maleVariant: One little mishack, happens even to the best. But no way to know for sure.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm. Unfortunately, we need hard evidence, not speculation.
Who's backin' Hansen then?
Someone's lookin' to spark a war?
So… an inside job. It's plausible. I see why you reached out.
Hansen – any idea who he's in bed with?
So, a cast of hawks squawking for war?
Rosalind has more enemies than you can count.
For some, the war never ended.
It's me. I need a cab, two people. Long ride.
No, no papers. Not this time.
Yeah… Dogtown. Waterfront, usual spot. Thanks.
Done. We should leave.
Best if we weren't together. V, you'll go five minutes after we do.
Come on.
Heh. Just like old times, isn't it?
I sincerely hope it isn't.
Five minutes, V. We talked about this.
V, you're compromising everyone's safety. Move.
The elevator's staying put till you leave.
So, how do we get out of this little corner of paradise?
Let's just say it'll be a bumpy ride.
Reed, I needn't remind you what this means for the NUS's national security.
Ahem…
Uh-huh…
Won't be easy.
No problem.
Rest easy. Can be real persuasive when I need to be.
Zeal's good, but don't wreak havoc. Not too much, not yet.
And you, V… whatever "bond"  you two have fails to explain why you're here in the first place.
I don't know how much they're paying, but you better ask yourself – is it worth it?
Eh, shit… Shoulda wiped those camera recordings. My bad.
entries.maleVariant: Mh, shit… Shoulda wiped those camera recordings. My bad.

entries.femaleVariant: Shoulda wiped those cam scrolls…
Not a bluff, V.
Huh. Gotta be the shortest FIA career ever. Might not be an agent, but you're definitely special, V.
As for you, V… You said in the car Songbird hired you, correct?
I don't know how much she's paying, but you'd better ask yourself – is it worth it?
